{
  "stem": "24212.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This was very freshly at the end of the war in that region-- officially not yet the end of the war, April.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we got all the files into the car.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there was one, two, three-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] three of them and me is four, and one more guy I don't remember-- the five of us, we didn't fit the car.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So the two of them organized motorcycles.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were two motorcycles and Czechoslovak Red Cross car.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, the two motorcycles played escort.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we just retraced Prague that way, you know, and we went.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we got through to every American checkpoint-- you know, they salute the Czech Red Cross-- until we got to a Czech border and there were the Russkies and say, what Czech Red Cross, [LAUGHS] you know.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Papers?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had no papers.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, luckily one of those doctors was smart, and he had some-- I don't know, booze, vodka-- not vodka-- whatever they sell in Germany-- and a couple of bottles to the Ivans and we went through.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And by 9th of May, we were in Prague.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The uprising just ended in Prague.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We came for the tail end.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And from then on, the story takes a very happy turn, in the sense that pretty soon I got-- well, I worked for the war crime investigation, which was interesting, for about a year.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then my professor said, we'll send you to America on a scholarship.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that's where the-- the long, happy end follows, you know, in the United States.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, because this doctor who was the head honcho in this Czechoslovak [LAUGHS] Red Cross venture was a friend of the head of the Czech war crime commission, which was by then founded-- or founded in those days.",
      "word_count": 38
    }
  ],
